  <h1>Freelance Pricing Guides</h1>
  <p>Our guides are written by Phoenix Reyes, a 10-year independent contractor, for freelancers at every stage — from setting rates for the first time to optimizing a mature practice. Each guide is reviewed for accuracy against current tax data and market benchmarks.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/how-to-set-freelance-rates">How to Set Your Freelance Rates: A Data-Backed Framework</a></h3>
  <p>A complete framework for calculating your minimum viable rate and target rate, grounded in your actual income goals and self-employment costs — not a rule of thumb or an arbitrary multiplier of your old salary.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/freelance-vs-employee-tax-comparison">Freelance vs. Employee: The True Cost Comparison</a></h3>
  <p>A side-by-side breakdown of what self-employment actually costs versus employment — taxes, benefits, overhead, and income stability — so you can make a fully informed comparison and set rates that actually achieve income parity.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/raising-your-freelance-rates">How to Raise Your Freelance Rates Without Losing Clients</a></h3>
  <p>A practical guide to the mechanics and psychology of rate increases — how to frame the conversation, how much to raise, which clients to raise first, and how to handle pushback without losing relationships.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/project-based-vs-hourly-pricing">Project-Based vs. Hourly Pricing: Which Is Better for Freelancers?</a></h3>
  <p>A detailed comparison of the two most common freelance pricing models — when each is appropriate, how to quote project fees accurately, and why most experienced freelancers move away from hourly billing over time.</p>

